498
00:29:11.016 --> 00:29:14.216
Are there more specific tumor-derived mediators to

499
00:29:14.256 --> 00:29:18.116
discover? And there is a number of mediators that

500
00:29:18.216 --> 00:29:20.436
have been described already.

501
00:29:22.136 --> 00:29:26.056
And it's not always clear to which extent they come from the tumor and the

502
00:29:26.116 --> 00:29:28.416
host. This is probably a mixture of things.

503
00:29:28.806 --> 00:29:32.396
And this is why in the review, we described this as a gradient

504
00:29:32.776 --> 00:29:36.516
with some factors being more clearly tumor derived and others

505
00:29:36.616 --> 00:29:36.976
are

506
00:29:37.896 --> 00:29:41.516
tumor as well as host derived or more host derived,

507
00:29:41.876 --> 00:29:45.836
that then eventually affect all these processes that lead to wasting

508
00:29:45.876 --> 00:29:49.476
in adipose tissue, like the lipolysis that I described and

509
00:29:49.576 --> 00:29:53.536
muscle atrophy and other systemic consequences of

510
00:29:53.896 --> 00:29:57.036
these tumor signals. But some years ago, we became

511
00:29:57.796 --> 00:30:01.076
interested in one factor from the ADAMTS-like protein.

512
00:30:01.156 --> 00:30:04.796
So these are secreted glycoproteins, and there's this ADAMTS-like 4.

513
00:30:05.156 --> 00:30:09.136
The expression in the tumor was associated with increased mortality for different

514
00:30:09.376 --> 00:30:12.516
cancer types that are also associated with cachexia.

515
00:30:12.936 --> 00:30:14.796
So we looked into this factor,

516
00:30:15.716 --> 00:30:19.416
which belongs to the ADAM family of metalloproteases but

517
00:30:19.456 --> 00:30:23.136
lacks the catalytic domain, so there is no enzymatic

518
00:30:23.216 --> 00:30:24.966
activity. So we looked into

519
00:30:25.016 --> 00:30:28.436
thelevels of this

520
00:30:28.496 --> 00:30:32.396
factor in different mouse models, and here are some of the main mouse

521
00:30:32.436 --> 00:30:36.416
models that we use, the C26 mouse models, where colon cancer cells are

522
00:30:36.456 --> 00:30:40.196
implanted subcutaneously, and this leads then to weight loss.

523
00:30:40.576 --> 00:30:41.896
And as a comparison, we used

524
00:30:41.976 --> 00:30:45.386
MC38-implanted mice,

525
00:30:46.056 --> 00:30:49.756
also a colon cancer cell line that grows similar tumors but does not

526
00:30:49.816 --> 00:30:53.676
induce cachexia. And when we compared the ADAMSLIK4 levels, there

527
00:30:53.696 --> 00:30:57.596
was a clearly increase of ADAMSLIK4 in the cachexia condition,

528
00:30:57.936 --> 00:31:01.216
but not in the MC38 or the PBS control mice.

529
00:31:01.676 --> 00:31:05.656
And this was also true for another genetic model of colon cancer,

530
00:31:07.376 --> 00:31:11.276
the APC model, where we have severe weight loss, and this was also

531
00:31:11.296 --> 00:31:15.256
associated with increased circulating ADAMSLIK4 levels.

532
00:31:15.716 --> 00:31:19.396
And similarly, in the LLC model, a lung cancer model

533
00:31:19.516 --> 00:31:23.145
where LLC cells are subcutaneously implanted, also

534
00:31:23.296 --> 00:31:26.296
here increased ADAMSLIK4. And when we

535
00:31:27.976 --> 00:31:31.516
correlated over all these models ADAMSLIK4

536
00:31:31.556 --> 00:31:35.396
levels with the relative body weight change, there was a significant

537
00:31:35.436 --> 00:31:39.136
correlation indicating that there might be indeed a link

538
00:31:39.456 --> 00:31:42.956
between ADAMSLIK4 and weight loss in these cachexia models.

539
00:31:43.336 --> 00:31:44.136
Then we looked into

540
00:31:44.956 --> 00:31:47.996
patient samples. Here, a colorectal cancer

541
00:31:49.016 --> 00:31:52.736
cohort. Here you see the effect of cachexia.

542
00:31:53.116 --> 00:31:57.046
So we stratified the patients for cachectic and non-cachectic patients.

543
00:31:57.346 --> 00:32:00.676
And also here there was a significant difference in ADAMSLIK4

544
00:32:00.736 --> 00:32:02.256
levels with cachexia

545
00:32:03.276 --> 00:32:05.056
patients showing increased levels.

546
00:32:05.556 --> 00:32:09.456
And when we then looked into the cachexia index

547
00:32:09.556 --> 00:32:13.496
that takes weight loss as well as BMI under consideration, there

548
00:32:13.536 --> 00:32:16.396
was also a correlation between ADAMSLIK4

549
00:32:16.956 --> 00:32:20.476
circulating levels and the degree of cachexia based on this

550
00:32:20.496 --> 00:32:21.116
cachexia

551
00:32:23.036 --> 00:32:26.816
index. Then we had the chance to look into the TRACER X

552
00:32:27.296 --> 00:32:27.716
data,

553
00:32:29.276 --> 00:32:33.216
which are also part of the CanCan consortium studying cachexia

554
00:32:34.296 --> 00:32:38.176
for lung cancer. Here you see the stratification for non-cachectic and

555
00:32:38.216 --> 00:32:42.016
cachectic patients. And also here we see a correlation

556
00:32:42.376 --> 00:32:45.966
or an induced levels of ADAMSLIK4 indicating that there might

557
00:32:46.336 --> 00:32:49.356
indeed be a link between ADAMSLIK4 and cachexia.

558
00:32:49.766 --> 00:32:52.736
And interestingly, in this cohort, we saw that

559
00:32:53.116 --> 00:32:56.876
patients with high

560
00:32:56.956 --> 00:33:00.796
circulating levels of ADAMSLIK4 had a

561
00:33:01.116 --> 00:33:04.886
worse overall survival. And interestingly, this was not

562
00:33:04.916 --> 00:33:08.856
true for disease-free survival, and we interpreted this in the

563
00:33:08.916 --> 00:33:12.776
way that this effect might be due to cachexia and

564
00:33:12.836 --> 00:33:16.736
not to cancer progression. And this is why we

565
00:33:16.776 --> 00:33:19.736
decided also to then study this further mechanistically.

566
00:33:20.076 --> 00:33:23.836
So the first thing we did, we overexpressed ADAMSLIK4 in these

567
00:33:23.876 --> 00:33:26.376
non-cachexia inducing MC38 cells.

568
00:33:26.796 --> 00:33:30.736
And here you see the induction of levels upon overexpression of

569
00:33:30.896 --> 00:33:34.716
ADAMSLIK4 in MC38 cells. And interestingly, in

570
00:33:34.756 --> 00:33:37.096
comparison to the parental cell line, which does not

571
00:33:37.976 --> 00:33:41.336
induce cachexia, these cells now gained the

572
00:33:41.456 --> 00:33:45.116
ability to induce cachexia. So they turned cachexigenic

573
00:33:45.156 --> 00:33:49.036
by overexpressing ADAMSLIK4, and this was related

574
00:33:49.136 --> 00:33:49.976
also to

575
00:33:51.216 --> 00:33:55.016
loss in fat as well as lean body mass or muscle mass.

576
00:33:55.376 --> 00:33:59.356
And there was also a significant decrease in cross-sectional area in

577
00:33:59.396 --> 00:34:03.376
the muscle of these cells, and we saw also an effect on grip strength as a

578
00:34:03.456 --> 00:34:05.536
functional readout of the muscle.

579
00:34:06.256 --> 00:34:07.516
And then we did the

580
00:34:08.377 --> 00:34:12.116
inverse experiment. We took this cachexia-inducing

581
00:34:12.196 --> 00:34:15.676
C26 cells and knocked down ADAMSLIK4.

582
00:34:15.696 --> 00:34:19.256
And then when you implant these cells, this resulted in reduced levels of

583
00:34:19.296 --> 00:34:22.656
ADAMSLIK4 in the tumor as well as

584
00:34:22.716 --> 00:34:26.457
circulation. It's not complete, but still, this was sufficient

585
00:34:26.796 --> 00:34:28.756
to ameliorate weight loss in this model.

586
00:34:28.846 --> 00:34:32.736
So knocking down ADAMSLIK4 reduced

587
00:34:32.776 --> 00:34:36.196
the capacity of these cells to induce cachexia, further

588
00:34:36.576 --> 00:34:39.976
confirming that this might be a real

589
00:34:40.136 --> 00:34:43.176
mediator of the wasting process. Here, the

590
00:34:43.536 --> 00:34:46.656
phenotypic characterization of the muscles.

591
00:34:47.616 --> 00:34:51.457
There is the loss in lean mass. This was completely rescued

592
00:34:51.836 --> 00:34:53.437
by knockdown of ADAMSLIK4

593
00:34:54.357 --> 00:34:58.276
in the tumor. The same was true for the cross-sectional area, complete

594
00:34:58.636 --> 00:34:59.656
rescue, and

595
00:35:00.856 --> 00:35:03.356
interestingly also for adipose tissue.

596
00:35:03.396 --> 00:35:06.936
You see the dramatic loss in adipose tissue, and this was

597
00:35:06.976 --> 00:35:07.736
ameliorated

598
00:35:08.676 --> 00:35:11.576
when we knocked down ADAMSLIK4 in the tumor.

599
00:35:11.986 --> 00:35:14.636
And eventually, this also then prolonged

600
00:35:15.276 --> 00:35:19.136
cachexia-free survival, here defined as the time point when

601
00:35:19.196 --> 00:35:23.056
we have to kill the mice due to the humane endpoint of weight loss.

602
00:35:23.516 --> 00:35:26.836
And this was strongly

603
00:35:27.296 --> 00:35:29.616
prolonged upon knockdown of this factor.

604
00:35:31.076 --> 00:35:34.776
Then we looked into the muscles to further characterize the molecular

605
00:35:34.876 --> 00:35:38.836
characteristics. Here you see main E3 ligases that are an

606
00:35:38.876 --> 00:35:42.536
important part of the atrophy process in the muscle.

607
00:35:42.576 --> 00:35:44.396
They are induced in the cachectic condition.

608
00:35:44.756 --> 00:35:48.226
When we knock down ADAMSLIK4 in the tumor, this was completely

609
00:35:48.296 --> 00:35:52.236
rescued. And the same was true also for factors involved in the autophagy

610
00:35:52.336 --> 00:35:55.756
process, another kind of process that is

611
00:35:55.796 --> 00:35:58.556
important for the wasting of muscle.

612
00:35:59.376 --> 00:36:03.356
And this was also reversed upon knockdown of ADAMSLIK4 in the

613
00:36:03.456 --> 00:36:05.836
tumor. And eventually, here you see the

614
00:36:06.776 --> 00:36:10.636
suppression of pathways that are

615
00:36:10.716 --> 00:36:14.676
induced in cachexia like autophagy and proteasomal

616
00:36:14.716 --> 00:36:18.116
degradation of proteins, and these were

617
00:36:18.156 --> 00:36:21.296
completely suppressed upon knockdown of

618
00:36:21.356 --> 00:36:25.156
ADAMSLIK4, showing that ADAMSLIK4

619
00:36:25.236 --> 00:36:28.876
was connected to an overall atrophic process in the

620
00:36:28.936 --> 00:36:32.370
muscle.So we asked how does this work and

621
00:36:32.860 --> 00:36:35.540
can we characterize the mechanism?

622
00:36:35.600 --> 00:36:39.140
So we took advantage of a technology called TRICEPS

623
00:36:39.220 --> 00:36:40.400
to kind of

624
00:36:41.400 --> 00:36:43.820
capture potential ligands for orphans.

625
00:36:44.280 --> 00:36:47.000
Adamslike4 here is the ligand, is kind of

626
00:36:47.980 --> 00:36:50.680
bound to this TRICEPS moiety, which

627
00:36:51.760 --> 00:36:53.020
includes a cross-linking

628
00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:57.800
part to cross-link with potential interactors on the cell

629
00:36:57.880 --> 00:37:01.600
surface of living cells, as well as a biotin leg for

630
00:37:01.620 --> 00:37:05.320
purification for further analysis by mass

631
00:37:05.400 --> 00:37:08.960
spectrometry. And when we did this experiment, we

632
00:37:09.000 --> 00:37:12.720
found pro-TGF beta as the main binding partner

633
00:37:12.820 --> 00:37:16.200
of Adamslike4 on myotubes.

634
00:37:16.800 --> 00:37:20.620
Here is shown the comparison to the positive control using

635
00:37:20.640 --> 00:37:21.280
transferrin,

636
00:37:22.420 --> 00:37:23.980
binding to the transferrin receptor.

637
00:37:24.400 --> 00:37:28.180
We have this kind of similar data also for a negative control.

638
00:37:28.580 --> 00:37:31.580
So this was a strong candidate, pro-TGF beta.

639
00:37:32.240 --> 00:37:35.960
So what is pro-TGF beta? This is the precursor transcribed from one

640
00:37:36.060 --> 00:37:36.440
gene,

641
00:37:37.320 --> 00:37:41.140
which is then processed in the ER and contains

642
00:37:41.220 --> 00:37:44.500
both the mature TGF beta growth factor as well as the

643
00:37:46.060 --> 00:37:49.910
latency associated peptide. So they are from one gene, are processed, but

644
00:37:49.960 --> 00:37:53.700
then stay together non-covalently bound and are transferred to the

645
00:37:53.720 --> 00:37:54.680
plasma membrane,

646
00:37:56.100 --> 00:37:59.980
where then TGF beta is stored in an inactive state and can be released

647
00:38:00.020 --> 00:38:03.560
from this complex then to activate the receptor

648
00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:07.080
and signal through the Smad signaling pathway.

649
00:38:07.740 --> 00:38:11.480
So we thought, okay, maybe Adamslike4 might interact with this complex.

650
00:38:12.800 --> 00:38:13.630
And the question was,

651
00:38:14.580 --> 00:38:18.520
in which way? And for this we did immunoprecipitations where

652
00:38:18.590 --> 00:38:21.940
we tried to kind of dissect whether

653
00:38:22.500 --> 00:38:26.460
Adamslike4 is binding to TGF beta itself or

654
00:38:26.500 --> 00:38:29.440
the LAP. And from this IP it was pretty clear that

655
00:38:30.280 --> 00:38:34.100
Adamslike4 was binding to the LAP but not to TGF

656
00:38:34.140 --> 00:38:37.340
beta itself. This we could confirm using

657
00:38:39.060 --> 00:38:43.020
a split luciferase assay where we used LAP with a

658
00:38:43.080 --> 00:38:46.740
large bead and Adamslike4 with a small bead of luciferase.

659
00:38:46.780 --> 00:38:50.640
When you put it together, then you have luciferase when there

660
00:38:50.680 --> 00:38:53.820
is an interaction, and this was exactly the case,

661
00:38:54.220 --> 00:38:56.280
confirming the IP result

662
00:38:58.020 --> 00:39:01.660
regarding the interaction of Adamslike4 with LAP.

663
00:39:02.200 --> 00:39:05.040
And this was also true when we used the whole cell lysate.

664
00:39:05.520 --> 00:39:09.500
And then if we do the assay similarly for TGF beta and LAP

665
00:39:10.280 --> 00:39:14.120
as a kind of inactive complex, when you

666
00:39:14.320 --> 00:39:16.400
put this together, then we have a signal.

667
00:39:16.760 --> 00:39:18.990
If we add Adamslike4, then the

668
00:39:19.060 --> 00:39:22.740
signal is reduced, indicating

669
00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:27.960
that the interference of Adamslike4 with LAP was reducing the

670
00:39:27.980 --> 00:39:30.800
interaction between TGF beta and LAP.

671
00:39:30.980 --> 00:39:33.220
So we think this is the mechanism of action,

672
00:39:35.460 --> 00:39:38.700
based on kind of an activation of TGF beta signaling.

673
00:39:39.500 --> 00:39:43.220
And this we could also show here, for instance, concerning the release of

674
00:39:43.240 --> 00:39:46.980
TGF beta upon treatment of myotubes with recombinant

675
00:39:47.040 --> 00:39:47.920
Adamslike4.

676
00:39:49.520 --> 00:39:52.720
TGF beta signaling results also in TGF beta expression.

677
00:39:52.800 --> 00:39:56.580
See, this is what you see here. When we treat myotubes with Adamslike4,

678
00:39:57.920 --> 00:40:01.800
TGF beta expression is induced. When we knock down TGF beta, this

679
00:40:01.940 --> 00:40:05.660
effect is abolished. And interestingly, this is also reflected at the level of

680
00:40:05.740 --> 00:40:09.460
myotube atrophy. This is the atrophy effect of the myotubes upon

681
00:40:09.900 --> 00:40:12.200
treatment with recombinant Adamslike4.

682
00:40:12.240 --> 00:40:16.200
This can be abolished upon knockdown of TGF beta.

683
00:40:16.230 --> 00:40:19.820
And similarly, we can also rescue this effect by

684
00:40:19.960 --> 00:40:22.639
small molecule inhibitors of the TGF beta receptor.

685
00:40:23.040 --> 00:40:26.950
Here you see the induction of Smad2 signaling upon treatment of myotubes

686
00:40:27.460 --> 00:40:31.120
with Adamslike4. This is completely abolished

687
00:40:31.180 --> 00:40:32.580
upon inhibition of the

688
00:40:34.180 --> 00:40:37.600
TGF beta receptor, and this is also reflected in the level

689
00:40:37.660 --> 00:40:41.080
of atrogin-1 expression. So the atrophy

690
00:40:41.140 --> 00:40:44.810
inducing factor, this expression is induced upon treatment with

691
00:40:44.820 --> 00:40:48.799
Adamslike4 and also reduced upon inhibition of the

692
00:40:48.859 --> 00:40:52.660
receptor. And this is also reflected in the phenotype

693
00:40:52.720 --> 00:40:56.480
of the myotubes. So Adamslike4 treatment induces

694
00:40:56.520 --> 00:41:00.020
myotube atrophy, and this can be counteracted by

695
00:41:00.060 --> 00:41:02.040
inhibiting the TGF beta receptor.

696
00:41:03.240 --> 00:41:05.260
Then we looked again into the

697
00:41:06.240 --> 00:41:10.100
tissue from the mice. We see that upon knockdown

698
00:41:10.140 --> 00:41:11.580
of Adamslike4 in the tumor,

699
00:41:12.400 --> 00:41:15.780
induction of TGF beta target genes is strongly

700
00:41:15.900 --> 00:41:19.810
reduced again in these livers. And interestingly, this is also associated

701
00:41:20.100 --> 00:41:23.900
with effects on fibrosis. I mean, TGF beta is known as an important

702
00:41:23.980 --> 00:41:27.800
factor for tissue fibrosis. We see muscle fibrosis in cachexia,

703
00:41:28.400 --> 00:41:31.200
and this effect is ameliorated upon knockdown of

704
00:41:31.240 --> 00:41:32.480
Adamslike4

705
00:41:33.440 --> 00:41:36.660
in the tumor. We then confirmed this in

706
00:41:36.700 --> 00:41:37.500
primary

707
00:41:39.440 --> 00:41:43.240
myotubes from human. Again, the effect of Adamslike4

708
00:41:43.340 --> 00:41:47.300
treatment to myotube atrophy can be abolished by

709
00:41:47.340 --> 00:41:50.880
treatment with a neutralizing antibody against TGF beta,

710
00:41:51.280 --> 00:41:54.680
and this is also reflected on the level of TGF beta

711
00:41:55.020 --> 00:41:55.920
target genes.

712
00:41:57.220 --> 00:42:01.060
Eventually, we had the chance to look into a subcohort of

713
00:42:01.880 --> 00:42:05.380
colon and pancreatic cancer patients, where we see

714
00:42:06.000 --> 00:42:09.820
again the induction of Adamslike4 related to

715
00:42:09.900 --> 00:42:12.860
the cachexia phenotype. And also here we see

716
00:42:12.920 --> 00:42:16.680
induced atrophy markers, TGF beta

717
00:42:17.500 --> 00:42:18.640
target genes and

718
00:42:19.700 --> 00:42:23.190
fibrosis related genes induced in the muscles of these

719
00:42:23.300 --> 00:42:23.760
patients.

720
00:42:24.760 --> 00:42:28.638
So, umI hope I could convince you that

721
00:42:28.668 --> 00:42:30.308
this might be an interesting factor.

722
00:42:30.428 --> 00:42:34.388
Circulating atoms like four levels are increased in cachexia and

723
00:42:34.608 --> 00:42:38.528
contribute to muscle and adipose tissue loss, and this is mediated through

724
00:42:38.588 --> 00:42:41.488
activation of TGF-beta signaling in the muscle.

725
00:42:42.168 --> 00:42:46.108
And this is why we think, at least for those patients with induced

726
00:42:46.148 --> 00:42:50.048
atoms like four levels, this might be an interesting target to

727
00:42:50.088 --> 00:42:53.608
counteract cachexia by a novel pharmacotherapy.

728
00:42:54.168 --> 00:42:57.988
And with this, I would like to end and acknowledge again Juliano, who did the

729
00:42:58.048 --> 00:43:02.008
work. I realized I don't have a current picture from my group, so I generated

730
00:43:02.088 --> 00:43:04.888
one. This is me, obviously, the older guy.

731
00:43:04.948 --> 00:43:07.728
This is Juliano and the others in my group.

732
00:43:07.808 --> 00:43:09.688
Thank you very much for your attention.

733
00:43:14.568 --> 00:43:16.448
Great talk.

734
00:43:16.928 --> 00:43:16.978
Thank you.

735
00:43:16.978 --> 00:43:20.548
So I guess therapeutically, do you think there'd be any advantage in targeting the

736
00:43:20.628 --> 00:43:23.768
atom protein you described versus just TGF-beta inhibition?

737
00:43:24.948 --> 00:43:27.648
Sorry, can you-- Yeah. I get it. Yeah,

738
00:43:28.408 --> 00:43:32.187
TGF-beta targeting is out there for some time, and to my

739
00:43:32.208 --> 00:43:33.568
knowledge, there is no really

740
00:43:34.808 --> 00:43:38.408
approved therapy, and this might be due to the pleiotropic

741
00:43:38.568 --> 00:43:41.968
functions of TGF-beta. So my hope would be that

742
00:43:42.128 --> 00:43:45.788
targeting atoms like four might be more specific to this cachexia

743
00:43:45.828 --> 00:43:49.408
condition related to increased levels and

744
00:43:49.488 --> 00:43:53.328
spare other TGF-beta dependent effects, and by this, be

745
00:43:53.988 --> 00:43:54.888
a way to go. Yeah.

746
00:43:56.788 --> 00:44:00.608
Really nice data. And Jessica Bauer from UCSD.

747
00:44:01.048 --> 00:44:04.688
I have a question. Did you also look for other receptors of the

748
