01:26:22.364 --> 01:26:26.284
is a sort of context that I'm excited about because obviously, as you

1453
01:26:26.344 --> 01:26:29.804
all know, mostly we use mathematical approaches and data

1454
01:26:29.814 --> 01:26:33.524
analysis to make sense of data that we have acquired, but this is actually

1455
01:26:33.884 --> 01:26:37.144
a paradigm where we can make predictions and then test against those predictions.

1456
01:26:37.984 --> 01:26:41.784
So these are the contributions that we've made that

1457
01:26:41.844 --> 01:26:45.644
I've summarized in this talk. I think we have now emerging

1458
01:26:45.704 --> 01:26:49.354
evidence that this anticancer immunity and autoimmunity are on the same spectrum,

1459
01:26:49.404 --> 01:26:53.304
and as a consequence, that autoimmunity can be the consequence of the cancer

1460
01:26:53.344 --> 01:26:56.904
that you never knew you had. And the effect by which this autoimmunity

1461
01:26:56.944 --> 01:27:00.184
declares itself can be very profound and can really be

1462
01:27:00.264 --> 01:27:02.104
changed brain function and

1463
01:27:02.184 --> 01:27:05.584
behavior as a consequence.

1464
01:27:06.064 --> 01:27:09.694
We see that there is a continuity here, that

1465
01:27:09.744 --> 01:27:13.154
this temporary inflammation, when it's not

1466
01:27:13.184 --> 01:27:15.064
resolving, actually leads to

1467
01:27:16.144 --> 01:27:20.084
progressive reprogramming of the host organism and then to cachexia, and

1468
01:27:20.164 --> 01:27:23.944
I think that's one of the open questions in the field, if you so wish.

1469
01:27:24.204 --> 01:27:28.104
What can we learn from cachexia about normal biology? Why has this evolved?

1470
01:27:28.144 --> 01:27:31.564
Is cachexia actually not maladaptive, but is

1471
01:27:31.664 --> 01:27:35.224
it unsustainable but adaptive?

1472
01:27:35.624 --> 01:27:37.764
I hope you see the difference between the two processes.

1473
01:27:38.164 --> 01:27:39.224
And again, if I

1474
01:27:40.444 --> 01:27:43.784
may take the liberty as the chair of the session, I would like to

1475
01:27:43.884 --> 01:27:45.824
suggest that it's probably the latter.

1476
01:27:45.944 --> 01:27:48.304
In other words, it's not a pathological process.

1477
01:27:48.704 --> 01:27:52.344
It is a biological process that over time becomes

1478
01:27:52.424 --> 01:27:56.184
unsustainable for the organism. And I'm not the first one to express this

1479
01:27:56.224 --> 01:28:00.194
idea, but that's where I would be leaning, rather than it saying it's

1480
01:28:00.224 --> 01:28:03.824
a completely dysregulated nonsense process that just drives

1481
01:28:03.944 --> 01:28:07.704
random disease. And then, the other contribution is that I think we are

1482
01:28:07.744 --> 01:28:11.444
beginning to understand how these systems interact sufficiently

1483
01:28:11.484 --> 01:28:15.104
deeply now to make real theoretical frameworks

1484
01:28:15.144 --> 01:28:19.084
available to reason about the whole body response to cancer, and those

1485
01:28:19.124 --> 01:28:20.604
frameworks are hopefully

1486
01:28:21.664 --> 01:28:25.104
transferable well beyond the acute

1487
01:28:25.164 --> 01:28:27.284
context of cancer-associated cachexia.

