01:30:34.044 --> 01:30:36.684
great. I have two questions. First, actually, about second part.

1524
01:30:37.084 --> 01:30:39.944
And I was a system biologist before, so really, really

1525
01:30:40.004 --> 01:30:43.264
appreciate the insight. If you talk to

1526
01:30:43.304 --> 01:30:47.004
clinicians, usually they say, "Oh, it's about reducing a tumor burden.

1527
01:30:47.224 --> 01:30:51.064
If you reduce a tumor burden, you're going to get better." So you are assuming this

1528
01:30:51.124 --> 01:30:55.044
kind of more linear relationship between tumor burden and the

1529
01:30:55.064 --> 01:30:58.824
cachexia. And here what you're saying is, if you're going through that path of no

1530
01:30:58.884 --> 01:31:02.264
return, it's not going to have that linear relationship

1531
01:31:03.024 --> 01:31:06.444
So my question is, if we're thinking about trying to revert that

1532
01:31:06.944 --> 01:31:10.574
condition, is it almost like a bistability?

1533
01:31:10.574 --> 01:31:11.364
It means

1534
01:31:12.364 --> 01:31:15.044
it's not just going back to the original level, then it's going to revert.

1535
01:31:15.184 --> 01:31:18.944
You almost have to do more to kind of try to pull it back, right?

1536
01:31:19.004 --> 01:31:22.764
If you think about a positive feedback, almost, the threshold is different if you

1537
01:31:22.784 --> 01:31:25.623
try to revert that condition. I'm just trying to see that.

1538
01:31:25.664 --> 01:31:26.694
Yeah. So those are

1539
01:31:27.804 --> 01:31:29.674
many questions, and I

1540
01:31:30.564 --> 01:31:34.464
appreciate your reasoning about them, and we think about, I think all of

1541
01:31:34.504 --> 01:31:36.204
us think about those questions

1542
01:31:37.644 --> 01:31:40.824
for many hours a day. I want to go systematically.

1543
01:31:40.924 --> 01:31:44.324
Firstly, the uncoupling of the tumor burden from the host response.

1544
01:31:44.484 --> 01:31:46.524
I think that I want to say two things about that.

1545
01:31:46.944 --> 01:31:50.464
It is more likely that as your cancer progresses and your tumor burden increases,

1546
01:31:50.484 --> 01:31:52.834
that you have systemic effects. I'm not disputing that.

1547
01:31:52.844 --> 01:31:55.804
Is it an absolute linear relationship? No.

1548
01:31:55.844 --> 01:31:59.724
We have clear evidence to the contrary that some people have massive tumor

1549
01:31:59.744 --> 01:32:03.004
burden and don't have any systemic effects, and some people have tiny tumors, as

1550
01:32:03.044 --> 01:32:04.724
far as we know, and have systemic effects.

1551
01:32:05.104 --> 01:32:08.984
In the clinic and also actually in neuro model systems, we sometimes see

1552
01:32:09.024 --> 01:32:10.064
complete uncoupling.

1553
01:32:11.384 --> 01:32:13.944
Tumors get bigger, mice get better, or vice versa.

1554
01:32:14.004 --> 01:32:16.484
So there's no definitive relationship.

1555
01:32:16.584 --> 01:32:20.404
But in first approximation, I think it holds true, and that gets me to the second

1556
01:32:20.484 --> 01:32:24.204
point, is what we are doing actually ultimately a standalone

1557
01:32:24.264 --> 01:32:27.054
effort, or should it be in the context of treating the cancer?

1558
01:32:27.084 --> 01:32:30.624
And I think all of us would agree that ultimately, of course, the elephant in the

1559
01:32:30.664 --> 01:32:33.224
room is to cure the cancer if we can,

1560
01:32:34.224 --> 01:32:38.064
because that will also, in no small parts, cure the organism.

1561
01:32:38.964 --> 01:32:42.744
The important bit here to think about is many patients who have cancer

1562
01:32:42.804 --> 01:32:46.384
progression, have systemic symptoms, are not well enough to get the systemic

1563
01:32:46.464 --> 01:32:48.504
treatments that we want to give them to cure the cancer.

1564
01:32:48.914 --> 01:32:52.004
And so I think one of the things by which we can reason about the whole body

1565
01:32:52.024 --> 01:32:55.654
response to cancer and what to do about it is through the therapeutic window.

1566
01:32:55.904 --> 01:32:59.714
So can we enable patients to be well enough to get all these

1567
01:32:59.744 --> 01:33:03.074
wonderful treatments that are being developed to push back against the cancer?

1568
01:33:03.124 --> 01:33:05.224
But I think it's a joint effort. Does that make sense?

1569
01:33:05.874 --> 01:33:05.874
Yes.

1570
01:33:05.884 --> 01:33:08.964
And then the question of hysteresis is an interesting question, and I have many

1571
01:33:08.984 --> 01:33:11.924
thoughts on that. And actually, you should speak to Alice, who's sitting in the row

1572
01:33:11.964 --> 01:33:15.864
behind you, because she's inadvertently done experiments about that,

1573
01:33:16.184 --> 01:33:18.943
and she sees that there is hysteresis in the system.

1574
01:33:18.984 --> 01:33:22.744
So in other words, if systems, at least model systems, develop

1575
01:33:22.804 --> 01:33:26.724
cachexia again, they develop it with a different dynamic than they did in

1576
01:33:26.764 --> 01:33:27.483
the first instance.

1577
01:33:28.144 --> 01:33:29.324
And then secondly, a quick question.

1578
01:33:29.484 --> 01:33:33.274
The first part of story, again, the beautiful nature paper on-- It's

1579
01:33:33.304 --> 01:33:35.674
puzzling that breast cancer is expressing those

1580
01:33:37.344 --> 01:33:37.984
embryonic

1581
01:33:38.844 --> 01:33:42.144
neural factors and that trigger that response.

1582
01:33:42.324 --> 01:33:42.804
Is

1583
01:33:43.664 --> 01:33:46.504
there a specific reason that breast cancer do that?

1584
01:33:46.604 --> 01:33:50.524
Or you think it's just a breast cancer turning on these fetal programs, and this is

1585
01:33:50.534 --> 01:33:54.364
just kind of byproduct of the breast cancer try to do EMT or the

1586
01:33:54.404 --> 01:33:57.224
breast cancer try to be more proliferative?

1587
01:33:57.324 --> 01:33:58.364
Yeah. Thank you for that question.

1588
01:33:58.404 --> 01:34:02.364
At the risk, again, of being slightly controversial, especially in the

1589
01:34:02.424 --> 01:34:05.204
context of AACR, I think about this disease site-agnostic.

1590
01:34:05.264 --> 01:34:08.084
I don't think this is restricted to breast cancer, to be absolutely clear.

1591
01:34:08.104 --> 01:34:08.224
Mm-hmm.

1592
01:34:08.364 --> 01:34:12.144
It is interesting to see, there is a very good paper from Jessica

1593
01:34:12.164 --> 01:34:15.924
Tolkun a couple of years back that ER is

1594
01:34:15.984 --> 01:34:19.444
one of the regulators for GluN2B

1595
01:34:19.504 --> 01:34:22.884
expression. So there might be a hormonal component, and so it might be

1596
01:34:22.904 --> 01:34:26.404
particularly predominant in patients with

1597
01:34:26.444 --> 01:34:29.604
triple-negative breast cancer. But again, I think this is

1598
01:34:30.064 --> 01:34:34.004
probably-- NMDA receptors get expressed in a multiplicity of cancers, and

1599
01:34:34.064 --> 01:34:38.004
it's only one example of an onco-neuroantigens. There are others.

1600
01:34:39.004 --> 01:34:39.404
Thanks.

1601
01:34:39.444 --> 01:34:39.704
Thank you.

